<TEXT>
a special commission created by gov mario 
cuomo called sunday for cuts in federal spending consideration of 
tax increases and a longer school year to deal with what it says is 
the countrys economic crisis 
the cuomo commission on trade and competitiveness said the 
nations leaders should consider a freeze on military spending 
taxing social security benefits of wealthier americans and a 
reduction of farm subsidies that benefit large producers 
the commission also recommmended higher taxes for luxury items 
and consideration of a 10perbarrel oil import fee and the 
imposition of a valueadded tax on goods and services the 
commission said that if adopted both the oil import fee and the 
valueadded tax should be structured to insulate the poor 
the commission believes that future fiscal policy must be 
based on a combination of reduced spending and increased revenue 
said the 259page report from the 20member task force that 
included businessmen labor leaders and economists 
the cuomo commission report is being published as a paperback by 
simon and schuster and will be available in book stores as early as 
monday said cuomo spokeswoman anne crowley 
cuomo once considered a potential 1988 democratic presidential 
candidate has been pushing economic reform for months in addition 
to creating the cuomo commission in january 1987 the new york 
governor led the drive for the national economic commission which 
was approved by president reagan in december 
the commission which is due to report after the november 
election is headed by former democratic party chairman robert 
strauss and republican drew lewis a former us secretary of 
transportation other members include chrysler chairman lee iacocca 
and new york financier felix rohatyn 
the national commission is to prepare recommendations on the 
national deficit trade imbalance third world debt and 
productivity the same issues dealt with by the cuomo commission 
the word crisis has been cheapened by too frequent use but 
no other word so well describes americas present situation the 
cuomo commission concluded either america will implement reforms 
that strengthen the international trading system and make the 
nation more competitive at home or it risks a long slow national 
decline 
the major problems facing the nation on the economic front are 
the trade deficit and the federal deficit according to the 
commission 
the commission said the united states must improve its 
production capabilities in part through greater employee 
participation work to improve living conditions and create new 
markets in the third world by among other things helping 
restructure debt payments for developing nations and stabilize the 
international monetary system 
repairing roads and bridges was given a high priority by the 
group as was giving the nations youth the tools with which to 
compete 
we need a longer school year said the commission 
japanese students attend school 240 days a year european 
students on average 220 days in the us the average school 
year is 180 days the shorter school year clearly places 
american students at an educational disadvantage 
