gunsalus who smoked two packs of pall malls daily worked at 
shipyard jobs that left him covered with asbestos jurors were told 
last week he died last year at age 55 after smoking since age 11 
in 1985 the surgeon general reported that people who work near 
asbestos are five times as likely to get lung cancer as people who 
do not come in contact with the substance smokers are 10 times 
more likely to get lung cancer than nonsmokers but people who 
